<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-003-244 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 608 894</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Dec 2 1991 n450 p52(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Microsoft enhances Mail for Windows; version 3.0 due 2Q 1992.andO;(Microsoft Corp. introduces Microsoft Mail for PC Networks 3.0)(Product Announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mardesich, Jodi.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Microsoft Corp will release Version 3.0 of its Microsoft Mail forPC Networks in the 2nd qtr of 1992.andP;  Enhancements will include animproved Windows client, an automatic directory synchronizationfeature, a task scheduler and a Message Finder facility thatfilters incoming messages according to the subject.andP;  The directorysynchronization file format will be published so that othervendors can support it in their products.andP;  The directory acceptsover 500,000 names, the file's capacity depends on availableserver hard-disk space.andP;  Directories on all Microsoft Mail serversare updated through a serialization and verification process forsecurity purposes.andP;  The product will cost $695 per server,including a single-workstation license.andP;  Workstation licensesbegin at $395 for five.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Ticker:    MSFT.andO;Product:   Microsoft Mail for PC Networks 3.0 (Electronic mail system)(Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionElectronic mail systemsSoftware packages.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>